            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-56-1725454352371-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork has had 30 min, remove the dish<strong> </strong>from the oven and add the <strong>chopped red pepper</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>return the dish to the oven for a final 30 min or until thick and saucy – this is your <strong>crispy pork belly & smoky sauce</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the <strong>remaining smoked paprika </strong>and <strong>dried oregano </strong>and mix everything together</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>wedges</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-55-1725454355907-x200.jpg",
